statenotes:
[10-May]
- Total numbers are updated to the final figure reported for 10th May.
- 665 cases added by MH govt. on 10th May due to data cleaning
- 143 cases added by MH govt. on 5th May due to data cleaning
- 796 cases added by MH govt. on 4th May due to data cleaning

[10-May]
Delhi will be releasing bulletins in the morning, containing data of the previous day. We will add that data to the date on which the report is released, rather than the previous day.

- Cases updated as per WB bulletin as it now provides total number of cases.
- Deaths due to comorbidities added to total deceased
- Zones updated as per WB bulletin
Total includes patients from other states.
Cases in Punjab were effectively reduced as some cases were added to 'central pool' as per the bulletin
One active case in KA reduced as a confirmed patient died of non-CoViD19 related reasons
Mahe native who expired in Kannur included in Kerala's tally

Includes one case from Nagaland
One patient who migrated to Bihar has been reduced from Active count
HP has 4 Migrated cases which are reduced from Active #. Also, death of Tibetan refugee is included in deceased numbers, but not in confirmed

state: Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu
